Java is a programming language.
It is designed by OOPS concept.
It is case sensitive language.
Java requires below mentioned environment : 
	JDK,
	--JAR--(Java Archieved Repository)
	--JRE--(Java Runtime Environment)
	--JVM--(Java Virtual Machine)
	--SRC--(Source file Repository) It contains only .java files.
	--BIN--(Binary (ByteCode file) File Repository) . It contains only .class file.
	 
 ---Class/Interface
     --Method
       --Instant method (User defined method or Normal method)
       --Main method 
 
 ---Data Type
     --No return value data type == void
     --Primitive data type == int,double,byte,boolean,short-(not used),long,float-(not used),char-(not used).
       Note : Primitive data type is mutable data type.
      --Non-Primitive data type == Array,Object,Class,Interface,String.
       Note : Non Primitive data type is immutable.
       
 ---Variable
    --Local variable
    --Instant or Global variable
    --Static variable
    
 ---Instant method
    --Constructor
    --Static method
    --Normal method
    --Abstract method
    --Method overloading
    --Method overriding
    
 ---Java Array and String
 ---Exception Handling
 ---Java Statement
   --If, If-Else,If-ElseIf&Else,Nested If
   --Looping statements (While,Do-While,For loop)
   --Switch case
   
 
    
    
    
       